-- Taiwan Equity Movers: AU Optronics, E Ink, Quanta Computer, UMC
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-05-09T05:47:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-09/taiwan-equity-movers-au-optronics-e-ink-quanta-computer-umc.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index fell 0.9 percent to 7,475.71, the
lowest close since Jan. 30.  AU Optronics Corp. (2409)  (2409 TT) retreated 1.9 percent to
NT$13.10. Taiwan’s second-largest flat panel maker said April
sales fell 6.2 percent from a year earlier to NT$29.17 billion,
according to a statement to the  Taiwan Stock Exchange .  E Ink Holdings Inc. (8069)  (8069 TT) slumped 6.8 percent to
NT$28.60, the lowest close since May 13, 2009. The company cut
salaries of executives by between 10 percent and 20 percent,
according to a statement to the Taiwan Stocks Exchange. It will
also implement unpaid leave for two days a month in May and
June, according to statement.  Quanta Computer Inc. (2382)  (2382 TT) lost 1.3 percent to
NT$80.80. The world’s largest laptop maker said April revenue
fell 22 percent from a year earlier to NT$67.76 billion ($2.3
billion), according to a statement filed to the Taiwan Stock
Exchange.  United Microelectronics Corp. (2303)  (2303 TT) slid 2 percent to
NT$14.45. The world’s second-largest maker of contract chips
said April sales fell 4.6 percent from a year earlier to NT$9.12
billion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
